WEBVTT

00:00:00.667 --> 00:00:02.533
<i> Do they always do this to you?</i>

00:00:02.667 --> 00:00:04.400
<i> I'm okay.</i>

00:00:04.567 --> 00:00:05.900
<i> Don't be afraid of me.</i>

00:00:06.767 --> 00:00:07.933
<i> I'll help you.</i>

00:00:09.133 --> 00:00:09.900
<i> Grace.</i>

00:00:11.400 --> 00:00:12.467
<i> Where's Grace?</i>

00:00:13.333 --> 00:00:14.367
<i> She was just here.</i>

00:00:16.067 --> 00:00:17.400
<i> "Teresa Lorenzo"?</i>

00:00:17.567 --> 00:00:20.200
<i> She's my father's aunt.</i>

00:00:20.333 --> 00:00:23.733
<i>Papa told me that I
should go to her.</i>

00:00:25.067 --> 00:00:25.867
<i> Grace?</i>

00:00:26.300 --> 00:00:26.967
<i> Grace!</i>

00:00:31.567 --> 00:00:32.467
<i> Aah!</i>

00:00:34.433 --> 00:00:35.967
<i>Two tickets to Quezon.
One adult, one child.</i>

00:00:38.333 --> 00:00:40.467
You must take after your father.

00:00:40.600 --> 00:00:42.500
<i>Because you don't
look like them.</i>

00:00:44.600 --> 00:00:48.800
<i>The first bus won't leave
until 5 AM.</i>

00:00:48.933 --> 00:00:49.733
<i> Thank you.</i>

00:00:49.867 --> 00:00:53.067
<i>Are you sure you'll
come with me?</i>

00:00:53.167 --> 00:00:56.067
<i>Don't you have
a flight to catch?</i>

00:00:56.167 --> 00:00:58.067
<i> I'll accompany you first.</i>

00:00:58.167 --> 00:01:00.400
<i>I want to make sure
you're safe.</i>

00:01:03.867 --> 00:01:10.733
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:49.500 --> 00:01:51.800 line:5%
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

00:01:51.900 --> 00:01:53.133 line:5%
[STOMACH GROWLING]

00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:05.800 line:5%
What is it?

00:02:05.900 --> 00:02:07.633 line:5%
I'm hungry.

00:02:13.500 --> 00:02:14.467 line:5%
Let's go.

00:02:15.467 --> 00:02:16.533 line:5%
We'll buy some food.

00:02:23.633 --> 00:02:30.667 line:5%
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:42.700 --> 00:02:43.700 line:5%
Grace?

00:02:47.300 --> 00:02:48.233 line:5%
Grace?!
[CAR HORN HONKING]

00:02:48.400 --> 00:02:49.600 line:5%
[TIRES SCREECHING]

00:02:50.333 --> 00:02:51.967 line:5%
You bastard! Hey!

00:02:52.100 --> 00:02:53.533 line:5%
[DRIVER] Are you trying
to kill yourself?

00:02:53.667 --> 00:02:55.133 line:5%
How about I kill you instead?!

00:02:55.267 --> 00:02:58.767 line:5%
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:02:58.900 --> 00:02:59.700 line:5%
Grace!

00:03:07.967 --> 00:03:10.033 line:5%
[PHONE RINGING]

00:03:11.400 --> 00:03:12.400 line:5%
Hello?

00:03:13.567 --> 00:03:15.100
Calm down!
I don't understand you!

00:03:17.133 --> 00:03:18.033
Fell into--

00:03:18.133 --> 00:03:22.900
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:03:23.100 --> 00:03:24.567
Alright, I'll be there.

00:03:26.500 --> 00:03:27.600
[WATER SPLASHES]

00:03:32.967 --> 00:03:36.067
Why did they let the kid
wander off?

00:03:36.167 --> 00:03:39.667
There's a thunderstorm
and the waves are strong.

00:03:41.033 --> 00:03:43.500
[BYSTANDER 1]
I heard it's not an accident.

00:03:43.633 --> 00:03:44.733
She might've jumped
into the sea.

00:03:44.867 --> 00:03:46.633
[BYSTANDER 2] You think
a kid would do that?

00:03:46.767 --> 00:03:48.600
Oh, but it's definitely
not an accident.

00:03:48.767 --> 00:03:50.733
Who knows, it could
have been premeditated.

00:03:50.867 --> 00:03:52.667
- That's right.
- Someone pushed her.

00:03:52.800 --> 00:03:57.067
[BYSTANDERS MURMURING]

00:03:57.233 --> 00:04:00.300
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:00.467 --> 00:04:03.700
[BYSTANDERS MURMURING]

00:04:03.833 --> 00:04:05.100
That must be her stuff.

00:04:05.200 --> 00:04:10.100
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:04:12.533 --> 00:04:14.200
Uh, miss...

00:04:15.700 --> 00:04:17.667
Some fishermen found these
at the sea earlier.

00:04:17.800 --> 00:04:19.633
I just want to confirm
if these are your daughter's.

00:04:19.800 --> 00:04:26.833
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:43.167 --> 00:04:50.000
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:05:08.100 --> 00:05:10.733
[ANNA] Hold on,
I'll just buy water.

00:05:11.367 --> 00:05:12.167
Just stay here.

00:05:15.867 --> 00:05:17.233
How much is this, mister?

00:05:19.233 --> 00:05:20.267
[ANNA] Two bottles, please.

00:05:21.467 --> 00:05:22.533
Good grief.

00:05:23.367 --> 00:05:24.667
- Ow.
- Let me help you.

00:05:24.800 --> 00:05:27.167
[OLD LADY GROANING, GRUNTING]

00:05:27.267 --> 00:05:28.200
My goodness.

00:05:29.300 --> 00:05:30.667
[GRUNTS]

00:05:30.767 --> 00:05:33.667
You're such a nice kid.
Thank you, dear.

00:05:33.800 --> 00:05:36.067
You're welcome.
Thank you, too.

00:05:36.233 --> 00:05:37.367
[OLD LADY] Thank you.

00:05:37.500 --> 00:05:39.133
My knees hurt.

00:05:40.933 --> 00:05:42.700
- Get in now.
- [OLD LADY] Peanuts for sale.

00:05:42.800 --> 00:05:47.600
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:48.800 --> 00:05:49.700
- Sarah. Sarah.
- What?

00:05:49.800 --> 00:05:50.700
Where are you going?

00:05:50.833 --> 00:05:52.300
I'll ask them for update.

00:05:52.433 --> 00:05:53.533
We've been here
for a day,

00:05:53.633 --> 00:05:55.700
and there's still no news
about Grace.

00:05:55.833 --> 00:06:00.233
Are you sure they saw Grace
fall into the water?

00:06:02.333 --> 00:06:03.400
Why?

00:06:03.567 --> 00:06:07.633
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:09.233
Hey, answer me!

00:06:09.367 --> 00:06:10.667
Why did you ask me that?

00:06:14.467 --> 00:06:15.600
Chito, come on.

00:06:16.767 --> 00:06:18.233
- What is it?
- There he is.

00:06:18.367 --> 00:06:19.267
Ask him.

00:06:21.267 --> 00:06:22.167
Sir.

00:06:22.300 --> 00:06:23.567
Any updates?

00:06:23.667 --> 00:06:25.000
Have you found my daughter?

00:06:25.800 --> 00:06:26.833
We'll give you an update later.

00:06:26.967 --> 00:06:28.800
We just have
a few questions first.

00:06:29.767 --> 00:06:31.300
When was the last time
you saw Grace?

00:06:32.667 --> 00:06:33.900
Yesterday.

00:06:34.433 --> 00:06:35.900
Yesterday morning.

00:06:36.033 --> 00:06:37.133
How was she?

00:06:38.333 --> 00:06:39.800
Pardon?

00:06:39.933 --> 00:06:42.067
What do you mean
how was she?

00:06:43.700 --> 00:06:46.767
[CHITO] Sir, what kind of
a question is that?

00:06:46.900 --> 00:06:50.133
Will that help find Grace?

00:06:50.300 --> 00:06:52.433
Where's Uncle Roman?
Bring him here!

00:06:52.567 --> 00:06:54.300
These are standard questions.

00:06:54.467 --> 00:06:56.333
We just want to know
what happened to Grace.

00:06:56.467 --> 00:06:57.767
It wasn't like that.

00:06:57.900 --> 00:06:59.667
We were okay
before she left.

00:07:00.667 --> 00:07:01.933
Then what was she
doing at the fish port?

00:07:02.067 --> 00:07:03.767
That kid's always sneaking out.

00:07:03.867 --> 00:07:06.133
But she eventually comes home.
She always does.

00:07:07.133 --> 00:07:09.833
Come on, Sarah.
Stop covering up for her.

00:07:09.967 --> 00:07:12.267
Sir, that kid
is really stubborn.

00:07:12.367 --> 00:07:13.833
She never listens to us.

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:16.633
She just runs off
and does whatever she pleases.

00:07:16.733 --> 00:07:18.800
When we tell her off,
she throws a tantrum

00:07:18.933 --> 00:07:20.633
and acts up even more.

00:07:20.733 --> 00:07:22.133
She's such a pain
to deal with.

00:07:22.267 --> 00:07:25.800
But if you're thinking
we neglected her,

00:07:25.933 --> 00:07:27.300
you're gravely mistaken.

00:07:28.533 --> 00:07:30.400
We are her parents.

00:07:30.533 --> 00:07:33.800
No matter what Grace does,
we love her very much.

00:07:35.233 --> 00:07:35.967
Right, Sarah?

00:07:36.067 --> 00:07:40.067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:40.200 --> 00:07:41.567
[TV NEWS REPORTER]
<i> The search is still ongoing</i>

00:07:41.700 --> 00:07:43.300
<i>for the child who allegedly
fell into the sea yesterday.</i>

00:07:43.433 --> 00:07:44.567
<i>The authorities are still
investigating</i>

00:07:44.700 --> 00:07:45.867
<i> what really happened,</i>

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:48.133
<i>if it was accidental
or there was foul play.</i>

00:07:52.567 --> 00:07:54.367
I'm sorry, ma'am, sir.

00:07:54.533 --> 00:07:55.933
We're just looking for someone.

00:07:56.067 --> 00:08:03.100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:08:13.633 --> 00:08:19.167
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:08:20.900 --> 00:08:24.500
Sir, we found the snatcher
hiding in the other bus.

00:08:25.667 --> 00:08:26.800
Alright.

00:08:27.433 --> 00:08:28.867
Sorry for the trouble.

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:36.033
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:43.733 --> 00:08:46.033
[TRAFFIC NOISE]

00:08:46.133 --> 00:08:48.533
[NARRATOR] For the past decade,

00:08:48.633 --> 00:08:51.533
<i> she has been your companion.</i>

00:08:51.633 --> 00:08:54.867
<i>She stood by your side
through every joyous</i>

00:08:55.033 --> 00:08:56.733
<i> and sad moment in life.</i>

00:08:56.867 --> 00:09:00.267
<i>She served as your voice
for decades now.</i>

00:09:00.433 --> 00:09:02.233
<i> She is your friend,</i>

00:09:02.333 --> 00:09:04.067
<i> defender,</i>

00:09:04.200 --> 00:09:05.633
<i> supporter,</i>

00:09:05.767 --> 00:09:09.000
<i>and the one and only
nation's mother</i>

00:09:09.133 --> 00:09:12.433
<i> and confidant for life.</i>

00:09:12.600 --> 00:09:14.167
[APPLAUSE, CHEERING]

00:09:14.300 --> 00:09:17.233
Thank you so much, everyone!

00:09:17.367 --> 00:09:20.133
Our program wouldn't
reach this milestone

00:09:20.267 --> 00:09:22.767
without you, our dear viewers.

00:09:22.933 --> 00:09:25.733
If there's something
that gives me strength

00:09:25.867 --> 00:09:30.267
to continue doing
all this as a mother,

00:09:30.467 --> 00:09:33.667
it's that I know I have you
all as my children.

00:09:33.800 --> 00:09:37.167
And I will help
and protect all of you.

00:09:37.300 --> 00:09:39.433
I love you so much, everyone.

00:09:39.567 --> 00:09:45.200
[APPLAUSE, CHEERING]

00:09:45.333 --> 00:09:47.700
When we return,

00:09:47.833 --> 00:09:50.767
we'll get to know the story
of Miss Mercy,

00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:53.867
a mother who got separated
from her daughter.

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:55.000
We'll be right back.

00:09:55.133 --> 00:10:01.967
[TV SHOW THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

00:10:03.667 --> 00:10:07.367
[MERCY] He even accused me
of having a lover.

00:10:08.833 --> 00:10:11.800
He has no idea about all
the hardships I went through

00:10:11.933 --> 00:10:14.067
while working abroad.

00:10:14.200 --> 00:10:16.800
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

00:10:16.900 --> 00:10:19.633
[MIRANDA] You haven't seen
your daughter in seven years.

00:10:19.767 --> 00:10:20.733
Yes.

00:10:21.733 --> 00:10:23.300
If she were here today,

00:10:23.433 --> 00:10:25.300
what would you like
to tell her?

00:10:25.433 --> 00:10:29.033
Dear, wherever you are
right now,

00:10:29.167 --> 00:10:31.500
if you're listening,

00:10:31.667 --> 00:10:34.567
remember that
I love you very much.

00:10:34.733 --> 00:10:37.333
Mama misses you so much.

00:10:37.433 --> 00:10:39.400
Jasmine, dear, come on out.

00:10:39.533 --> 00:10:41.833
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]
[GUEST SNIFFLES]

00:10:41.933 --> 00:10:45.933
Oh, my dear daughter!
[BOTH CRYING]

00:10:46.633 --> 00:10:48.400
[JASMINE SOBBING]

00:10:48.533 --> 00:10:52.100
[BOTH SOBBING, SNIFFLING]

00:10:52.233 --> 00:10:54.333
Oh, my dear...

00:10:54.433 --> 00:10:57.033
[SOBBING]
I've missed you so much.

00:10:57.200 --> 00:11:00.367
Thank you for joining us today.

00:11:00.533 --> 00:11:01.500
Let's meet again tomorrow.

00:11:01.633 --> 00:11:03.267
This has been Miranda Valdez.

00:11:03.400 --> 00:11:05.833
[AUDIENCE] The nation's mother!

00:11:05.933 --> 00:11:06.567
[CHEERING]

00:11:06.733 --> 00:11:09.000
[MIRANDA]
Your confidant for life.

00:11:09.167 --> 00:11:15.433
[TV SHOW THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

00:11:15.567 --> 00:11:19.533
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]
[RAIN POURING]

00:11:19.633 --> 00:11:21.133
I'm scared, Chito.

00:11:21.267 --> 00:11:22.933
We shouldn't have lied
to the cops.

00:11:23.067 --> 00:11:26.567
What are you talking about, huh?
We didn't lie.

00:11:26.733 --> 00:11:28.900
It's true that we love Grace.

00:11:29.067 --> 00:11:32.367
We feed her, clothe her,
and send her to school.

00:11:32.467 --> 00:11:35.033
We take good care of her.
We love Grace.

00:11:35.167 --> 00:11:36.867
- We hurt her!
- Shh!

00:11:36.967 --> 00:11:37.867
[WHIMPERS]
Shut up.

00:11:37.967 --> 00:11:39.367
Keep it down.
Others might hear you.

00:11:39.500 --> 00:11:40.367
[GRUNTS]

00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:41.600
Okay?

00:11:41.767 --> 00:11:43.800
We were just trying
to discipline her.

00:11:43.933 --> 00:11:46.267
That's what parents should
do to their children.

00:11:46.433 --> 00:11:48.500
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

00:11:48.633 --> 00:11:52.600
Do you want the cops
to know the truth?

00:11:52.767 --> 00:11:55.667
Should we tell them you hit her
before she went missing?

00:11:56.667 --> 00:11:59.300
If you want to go to jail,
suit yourself!

00:11:59.433 --> 00:12:01.233
What are you saying?
I'm not going to jail.

00:12:01.367 --> 00:12:03.333
- I didn't kill Grace.
- Even so.

00:12:03.467 --> 00:12:05.400
Use your brain!
You can still go to jail.

00:12:05.533 --> 00:12:09.067
They'll blame you for what
happened to Grace.

00:12:09.167 --> 00:12:11.733
It's the parents who
are held responsible

00:12:11.867 --> 00:12:13.400
if something happens
to their children,

00:12:13.500 --> 00:12:14.800
whether it's an accident
or not.

00:12:15.833 --> 00:12:17.767
So, if you don't want
to end up in jail,

00:12:17.867 --> 00:12:19.700
you better get a hold
of yourself, Sarah.

00:12:19.833 --> 00:12:21.700
Keep your mouth shut.

00:12:22.967 --> 00:12:25.333
No one should know what
we did to Grace,

00:12:25.467 --> 00:12:26.467
especially the cops.

00:12:26.633 --> 00:12:27.667
Is that clear?

00:12:27.800 --> 00:12:31.533
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:12:31.667 --> 00:12:33.500
I'm doing this for your
own good, Sarah.

00:12:34.700 --> 00:12:37.167
I know how hard it is
to be in jail.

00:12:38.667 --> 00:12:40.100
I don't want you
to experience that.

00:12:41.867 --> 00:12:43.000
I love you so much, Sarah.

00:12:43.133 --> 00:12:50.100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

00:12:54.500 --> 00:12:56.633
Congratulations!
[MIRANDA CHUCKLES]

00:12:56.767 --> 00:12:58.967
- Another year!
- Thank you!

00:12:59.100 --> 00:13:01.067
And in addition to that,

00:13:01.200 --> 00:13:02.667
the results are out.

00:13:02.833 --> 00:13:05.133
You got the Best Public Affairs
Program Host award.

00:13:05.233 --> 00:13:06.633
[MIRANDA CHUCKLES]
Congratulations, Miranda!

00:13:06.767 --> 00:13:08.533
You did it again!

00:13:08.667 --> 00:13:10.533
You're one proud manager
again, aren't you?

00:13:10.667 --> 00:13:12.333
Well, I'm more proud
of you as a friend.

00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:13.833
Aww.
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:16.300
This calls for a celebration.

00:13:16.400 --> 00:13:17.700
Where do you want
to celebrate?

00:13:17.833 --> 00:13:20.533
Leave all the preparations
to me. I know what you want.

00:13:21.400 --> 00:13:23.000
My dear, dear, Tommy.

00:13:23.133 --> 00:13:24.533
Let me remind you again.

00:13:24.700 --> 00:13:26.333
You're my associate producer.

00:13:26.467 --> 00:13:30.167
Leave all that kind of job
to my personal staff, okay?

00:13:30.300 --> 00:13:33.333
But Jessica and I are best
friends, Miss Miranda.

00:13:33.433 --> 00:13:34.733
Let me do this for you.

00:13:34.867 --> 00:13:37.867
You know you inspire me
and I'm your number one fan.

00:13:38.033 --> 00:13:39.533
Wait. Excuse me.

00:13:39.700 --> 00:13:40.867
You're her number two fan.

00:13:41.033 --> 00:13:43.900
[LAUGHTER]
I'm the number one.

00:13:44.033 --> 00:13:46.933
Remember that. Did you
do what I asked you?

00:13:47.067 --> 00:13:49.367
Oh, right. Not yet.
Excuse me, Miss Miranda.

00:13:49.533 --> 00:13:52.000
[LAUGHTER]

00:13:52.133 --> 00:13:59.500
[APPLAUSE, CHEERING]

00:13:59.633 --> 00:14:00.733
- Congrats, ma'am!
- Thank you.

00:14:00.900 --> 00:14:03.200
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]
[APPLAUSE, CHEERING]

00:14:03.300 --> 00:14:06.033
Let's set an appointment
with Perry for my gown.

00:14:06.133 --> 00:14:08.933
- But nothing too fancy.
- Oh, I know.

00:14:09.067 --> 00:14:11.200
- Simplicity is the best policy.
- Of course.

00:14:11.300 --> 00:14:12.733
Thanks again.

00:14:12.900 --> 00:14:15.533
I think you're the most handsome
among all the marshals here.

00:14:15.633 --> 00:14:17.933
- But still regal and elegant.
- Of course.

00:14:18.067 --> 00:14:21.800
I'll also call the nail salon
and set an appointment for you.

00:14:21.933 --> 00:14:25.400
You might get bashed if people
see your cracked nails.

00:14:25.567 --> 00:14:27.900
- Yours look more cracked.
- Of course not.

00:14:28.100 --> 00:14:29.733
My nails look good.
Look.

00:14:29.867 --> 00:14:36.300
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:14:36.433 --> 00:14:38.233
[ASHLEY] Hi! Good evening!

00:14:40.767 --> 00:14:42.767
Good evening, Madam Miranda.

00:14:42.933 --> 00:14:45.400
- I'm Ashley.
- Good evening.

00:14:45.533 --> 00:14:48.667
It's so nice to meet you,
Madam Miranda.

00:14:48.800 --> 00:14:51.900
Sorry, Ashley.
Can you leave us for a while?

00:14:52.033 --> 00:14:53.400
Just get a photo
with Miranda later.

00:14:53.500 --> 00:14:54.933
- But--
- Come on.

00:14:55.100 --> 00:14:57.900
I'll see you out.
Go wait outside, okay?

00:15:03.067 --> 00:15:05.267
[CARMEN] My goodness!
[DOOR SLAMS]

00:15:07.633 --> 00:15:09.433
I'm sorry, Miranda.

00:15:09.533 --> 00:15:11.833
I'll talk to the head
of security.

00:15:11.967 --> 00:15:14.033
I promise this won't
happen again.

00:15:14.167 --> 00:15:15.000
I don't mind,

00:15:15.133 --> 00:15:18.933
but of course, I want us
all to be safe.

00:15:19.967 --> 00:15:23.167
Do you remember when I was
interviewing President Caballero

00:15:23.300 --> 00:15:26.800
and an assassin suddenly
broke into the room?

00:15:26.967 --> 00:15:31.000
Uncle, we already helped you
put up your business, remember?

00:15:31.133 --> 00:15:33.300
But it was closed down after a
few months

00:15:33.467 --> 00:15:35.033
because of your negligence.

00:15:36.567 --> 00:15:38.867
Alright. I'll talk
to Mom.

00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:41.833
Good evening, Aunt Carmen!

00:15:42.000 --> 00:15:44.333
- Hi, baby.
- Hi!

00:15:45.700 --> 00:15:47.467
I heard you won an award again.

00:15:47.600 --> 00:15:48.700
I did!

00:15:48.833 --> 00:15:50.333
- Congratulations, Mom.
- Thank you, baby.

00:15:50.500 --> 00:15:51.467
Thank you so much.

00:15:51.567 --> 00:15:53.000
Thank you, thank you.

00:15:55.333 --> 00:15:57.700
Who were you talking to
on the phone earlier?

00:15:57.833 --> 00:16:00.133
Oh! That was Uncle Delfin.

00:16:00.233 --> 00:16:01.000
Oh.

00:16:01.167 --> 00:16:02.967
He's eyeing a vacant lot
in Batangas

00:16:03.100 --> 00:16:05.000
that he wants to develop
into a resort.

00:16:06.167 --> 00:16:08.367
He's asking if he could
borrow money from you.

00:16:08.533 --> 00:16:09.500
Sure.

00:16:09.633 --> 00:16:10.700
Mom!

00:16:10.867 --> 00:16:12.333
Here we go again.

00:16:12.433 --> 00:16:14.333
Dear, he's family.

00:16:14.467 --> 00:16:17.267
We're working hard
for our family, aren't we?

00:16:17.400 --> 00:16:18.533
Give him the money.

00:16:18.700 --> 00:16:20.333
Fine! Fine.

00:16:21.233 --> 00:16:22.033
But...

00:16:22.200 --> 00:16:24.033
- Mm?
- I'll have to check...

00:16:25.033 --> 00:16:26.767
...the lot first, okay?

00:16:26.900 --> 00:16:29.367
I have to make sure
the title is clean.

00:16:29.533 --> 00:16:33.667
I don't want them getting
scammed again like last time.

00:16:33.767 --> 00:16:37.100
They can't always
rely on you.

00:16:37.233 --> 00:16:38.533
Thank you, dear.

00:16:38.700 --> 00:16:41.733
I'll leave you two alone.

00:16:41.900 --> 00:16:45.767
I need to have a word
with security.

00:16:45.900 --> 00:16:47.433
[LAUGHING]
Oh, she never changes.

00:16:47.567 --> 00:16:48.467
My goodness.

00:16:48.600 --> 00:16:50.933
[JESSICA SIGHS DEEPLY]

00:16:51.067 --> 00:16:54.867
So, I have a case
you can use on your show.

00:16:54.967 --> 00:16:56.867
- Hmm?
- I've mentioned it to Julius.

00:16:56.967 --> 00:16:59.033
- That's good.
- Speaking of which...

00:16:59.167 --> 00:17:02.900
- Hmm?
- Can we have dinner with him?

00:17:03.067 --> 00:17:05.267
I just need to
tell you something.

00:17:06.233 --> 00:17:07.267
Sure.

00:17:07.400 --> 00:17:10.767
But I don't think I'll be free
anytime soon.

00:17:11.500 --> 00:17:13.200
It's important, Mom.

00:17:15.100 --> 00:17:16.967
Speak of the devil.

00:17:17.867 --> 00:17:19.900
- Miss Miranda.
- Hello.

00:17:21.033 --> 00:17:23.400
Babe, you're too formal.

00:17:23.500 --> 00:17:25.567
You don't have to treat
Mommy like your boss

00:17:25.667 --> 00:17:26.967
when it's just us around.

00:17:27.633 --> 00:17:28.600
Jessica.

00:17:28.767 --> 00:17:32.333
I was just telling Mom
about dinner.

00:17:32.467 --> 00:17:34.567
Well, that can wait.

00:17:34.700 --> 00:17:36.467
The higher-ups
want to see you.

00:17:36.600 --> 00:17:37.600
Ah.

00:17:37.767 --> 00:17:39.133
I think I know why.

00:17:39.933 --> 00:17:41.467
They probably want to
congratulate us

00:17:41.600 --> 00:17:43.400
because I won another award.

00:17:43.500 --> 00:17:44.800
I'll just change.

00:17:48.800 --> 00:17:55.833
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:21.000
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:18:29.033 --> 00:18:29.900
[DOOR OPENS]

00:18:32.000 --> 00:18:38.833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:18:48.400 --> 00:18:49.333
Miranda.

00:18:50.033 --> 00:18:53.800
This is Ashley Santillan,
our new host.

00:18:55.067 --> 00:18:56.167
Hi.

00:18:56.267 --> 00:18:57.567
Hi, Madam Miranda.

00:18:58.733 --> 00:19:00.200
"Miss Miranda" is fine.

00:19:01.133 --> 00:19:02.533
We've already met.

00:19:02.700 --> 00:19:03.867
What show is she doing?

00:19:04.400 --> 00:19:05.533
Yours.

00:19:06.433 --> 00:19:11.700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:19:11.800 --> 00:19:12.700
Excuse me?

00:19:14.100 --> 00:19:15.267
Thank you, Ashley.

00:19:15.400 --> 00:19:17.067
We'll just talk to Miranda.

00:19:19.967 --> 00:19:20.867
Excuse me.

00:19:24.567 --> 00:19:31.600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:19:35.633 --> 00:19:38.400
Is this a joke? It's not funny.

00:19:38.567 --> 00:19:40.867
Just one segment, Miranda.

00:19:41.467 --> 00:19:42.733
While you're
the Nation's Mother.

00:19:42.833 --> 00:19:46.233
Ashley is
the Nation's Big Sister.

00:19:46.400 --> 00:19:49.200
She will be the voice
of today's youth,

00:19:49.300 --> 00:19:50.900
providing a different
perspective.

00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:54.200
Plus, she has a good following
on social media.

00:19:54.300 --> 00:19:55.467
Haven't you heard already?

00:19:55.600 --> 00:19:57.067
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

00:19:57.233 --> 00:19:59.733
Miranda just won an award

00:19:59.900 --> 00:20:03.467
as the best public affairs
program host.

00:20:03.633 --> 00:20:06.267
- For ten consecutive years.
- Yes.

00:20:06.433 --> 00:20:08.100
[MAN]
But have you seen the ratings?

00:20:08.267 --> 00:20:11.800
There are days when you lose
to your rival show.

00:20:11.967 --> 00:20:14.667
We suggested that
you copy their format,

00:20:14.800 --> 00:20:16.467
but you opposed to it strongly

00:20:16.633 --> 00:20:18.067
because you didn't
want any fights.

00:20:18.967 --> 00:20:20.767
You wanted to stick
to your format.

00:20:20.867 --> 00:20:23.800
To be honest, the format
of your show is outdated.

00:20:24.867 --> 00:20:27.933
Where's the grit?
Where's the vigor?

00:20:28.967 --> 00:20:31.067
But it's still better than
an all-gimmick, rigged show.

00:20:31.167 --> 00:20:32.933
It's fine, Julius.

00:20:34.333 --> 00:20:35.933
Let me just tell you one thing.

00:20:37.900 --> 00:20:40.633
There's a reason why my show
has been going on for so long.

00:20:41.800 --> 00:20:43.633
And ever since,

00:20:43.733 --> 00:20:46.300
we never had to resort
to cheap gimmicks or tricks

00:20:46.400 --> 00:20:47.767
to keep the show on top.

00:20:47.867 --> 00:20:51.633
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:20:51.800 --> 00:20:53.200
It's public service.

00:20:53.333 --> 00:20:54.633
Not circus.

00:21:01.233 --> 00:21:03.767
[RAIN PATTERING]

00:21:03.867 --> 00:21:04.800
Uh...

00:21:05.700 --> 00:21:07.200
[FISHERMAN] Hurry.

00:21:07.333 --> 00:21:09.300
Uh, I'm begging you.

00:21:09.500 --> 00:21:11.200
Please help me look
for my daughter.

00:21:11.367 --> 00:21:12.833
The authorities have stopped
their search and rescue efforts.

00:21:13.000 --> 00:21:14.467
Well...

00:21:14.567 --> 00:21:16.067
we're willing to help you
look for her,

00:21:16.200 --> 00:21:18.667
but as you can see,
the weather is very bad.

00:21:19.167 --> 00:21:21.000
We might end up in danger.
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:21:21.167 --> 00:21:23.567
We also have families
that rely on us.

00:21:23.700 --> 00:21:25.500
You might be able
to save my daughter.

00:21:25.667 --> 00:21:26.867
Please help me.

00:21:27.033 --> 00:21:27.867
You see...

00:21:28.033 --> 00:21:30.067
we've been fishing
for many years.

00:21:30.200 --> 00:21:33.667
And in cases like that,
it's most likely that...

00:21:34.100 --> 00:21:35.367
Most likely what?

00:21:35.533 --> 00:21:36.800
Huh?

00:21:36.900 --> 00:21:38.133
It's most likely that
my daughter is dead?

00:21:38.867 --> 00:21:40.500
My daughter is not yet dead!

00:21:41.400 --> 00:21:43.167
Otherwise, you should've
already found her body.

00:21:43.300 --> 00:21:44.933
Take back what you said.

00:21:45.067 --> 00:21:46.667
- Take back what you said!
- Sarah!

00:21:46.767 --> 00:21:48.900
- What?!
- Come here. Calm down.

00:21:49.067 --> 00:21:52.000
No! You just want
something from us!

00:21:52.100 --> 00:21:54.200
What do you want? Money?
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:21:54.300 --> 00:21:55.233
- Stop this!
- No!

00:21:55.400 --> 00:21:56.367
They want to milk money from us!

00:21:56.467 --> 00:21:57.700
- Shut up!
- Why?

00:21:57.867 --> 00:22:01.000
Don't lash out at them.
That won't be of any help!

00:22:01.100 --> 00:22:03.900
No! I won't stop
until my daughter is found.

00:22:04.067 --> 00:22:05.333
You hear that?

00:22:05.433 --> 00:22:06.700
- Ouch!
- Stop this!

00:22:06.800 --> 00:22:08.367
What's with you?

00:22:08.900 --> 00:22:10.333
Get a hold of yourself!

00:22:10.433 --> 00:22:13.333
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
[SOBBING]

00:22:13.433 --> 00:22:15.700
I won't stop.

00:22:15.833 --> 00:22:19.100
I'll keep searching
until I find my daughter.

00:22:20.233 --> 00:22:23.800
Ever since I got pregnant
with Grace, what happened?

00:22:23.933 --> 00:22:26.633
People kept saying
nasty things about me!

00:22:27.933 --> 00:22:31.233
"Oh, Sarah? She's been a flirt
since she was young."

00:22:32.967 --> 00:22:35.800
"Sarah is so stubborn
and stupid!"

00:22:36.767 --> 00:22:37.933
"She won't amount to anything!"

00:22:38.100 --> 00:22:39.233
And now, what?

00:22:41.000 --> 00:22:42.467
My daughter is missing.

00:22:42.600 --> 00:22:46.633
Stop crying.
Don't waste your tears, okay?

00:22:47.833 --> 00:22:49.267
What if...
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

00:22:49.467 --> 00:22:51.933
your daughter didn't really
fall into the sea?

00:22:52.033 --> 00:22:53.667
What if she's just
wandering around?

00:22:53.800 --> 00:22:56.267
Someone saw my daughter
fall into the sea!

00:22:56.433 --> 00:22:58.833
What if they were mistaken?

00:22:58.967 --> 00:23:01.433
Couldn't they have seen wrong?

00:23:01.833 --> 00:23:04.267
Don't yell at me!

00:23:04.367 --> 00:23:06.967
You're acting strange.
Do you know anything? Huh?

00:23:07.133 --> 00:23:08.567
Is there something
you're not telling me?

00:23:08.667 --> 00:23:11.267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:23:11.367 --> 00:23:14.800
Earlier, you called me, right?

00:23:14.967 --> 00:23:17.100
You said your daughter
fell into the sea.

00:23:17.800 --> 00:23:18.833
I saw her, Sarah.

00:23:18.967 --> 00:23:21.433
I think I saw her... alive.

00:23:23.700 --> 00:23:26.133
[SOBBING]

00:23:26.300 --> 00:23:27.767
You bastard!

00:23:27.867 --> 00:23:31.000
You saw my daughter,
but you didn't tell me?

00:23:31.167 --> 00:23:32.967
Didn't you say on the phone

00:23:33.133 --> 00:23:35.167
that your daughter
fell into the sea?

00:23:35.333 --> 00:23:36.800
What did you expect?

00:23:36.967 --> 00:23:38.333
Of course,
I second-guessed myself!

00:23:39.500 --> 00:23:40.533
What if I was mistaken?

00:23:40.667 --> 00:23:42.467
You shameless bastard.

00:23:42.633 --> 00:23:44.533
Look at you.
You're so stupid!

00:23:44.667 --> 00:23:46.267
You're driving me crazy!

00:23:47.833 --> 00:23:49.867
I've been going crazy
looking for my daughter,

00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:52.133
but you didn't even
bother to tell me?

00:23:52.300 --> 00:23:53.467
You just kept silent?

00:23:53.633 --> 00:23:54.967
You didn't intend
to say anything?

00:23:55.100 --> 00:23:56.833
What if that really
was my daughter?

00:23:57.833 --> 00:24:00.367
Well then, congrats!
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:24:00.533 --> 00:24:02.167
Okay? Your daughter is alive!

00:24:03.500 --> 00:24:05.300
But I'm telling you, Sarah...

00:24:05.867 --> 00:24:08.333
Don't you dare tell the police.

00:24:08.433 --> 00:24:09.833
Do you understand?

00:24:09.933 --> 00:24:13.000
- And why is that, huh?
- You want to know why?

00:24:13.100 --> 00:24:14.967
What if they do find Grace?

00:24:15.067 --> 00:24:18.633
How would you explain
all the bruises on her body

00:24:18.733 --> 00:24:21.400
caused by your beating?

00:24:22.733 --> 00:24:25.000
If the police ask her, Sarah,

00:24:25.933 --> 00:24:27.467
we'll end up behind bars.

00:24:27.567 --> 00:24:28.700
Do you understand me?

00:24:28.900 --> 00:24:33.367
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:24:36.133 --> 00:24:42.933
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

00:24:52.100 --> 00:24:57.000
Teacher, I need to pee
and drink some water.

00:24:58.367 --> 00:24:59.533
Alright.

00:25:02.400 --> 00:25:03.700
Come on.

00:25:06.600 --> 00:25:08.067
Don't leave my side, okay?

00:25:08.967 --> 00:25:10.367
- [GRACE] Okay.
- [ANNA] Come on.

00:25:12.167 --> 00:25:13.067
Hold my hand.

00:25:16.133 --> 00:25:17.733
Hold on,
you're squishing the kid!

00:25:17.900 --> 00:25:19.467
- [MAN] Mind the kid!
- Hey! Hey!

00:25:19.600 --> 00:25:20.600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:25:20.733 --> 00:25:22.267
Hey! That's mine!

00:25:23.067 --> 00:25:23.967
Give it back!

00:25:24.600 --> 00:25:25.900
Go ahead! I dare you!

00:25:27.600 --> 00:25:29.800
- Look over there.
- Teacher, are you okay?

00:25:29.933 --> 00:25:36.967
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:25:49.600 --> 00:25:51.733
The search begins.

00:25:51.833 --> 00:25:54.233
I assure you, this is the story
<i> we've been looking for.</i>

00:25:54.333 --> 00:25:57.100
<i>Well then, give me more
to this story, Julius.</i>

00:25:57.267 --> 00:25:58.667
<i>Why was the kid there
in the first place?</i>

00:25:58.800 --> 00:26:00.900
<i>Are you trying
to blame the mother?</i>

00:26:01.033 --> 00:26:02.600
Desperately trying to escape...

00:26:02.767 --> 00:26:05.633
<i>Someone told the reporter
that we hurt Grace.</i>

00:26:05.767 --> 00:26:07.100
<i>Now, the police are
suspicious of me.</i>

00:26:07.267 --> 00:26:09.733
<i>They think I was physically
abusing Grace!</i>

00:26:09.867 --> 00:26:11.767
<i>We need to find Grace
before the police does.</i>

00:26:11.867 --> 00:26:13.767
...from the truth.

00:26:13.867 --> 00:26:15.600
<i>It was Teacher Anna
who first suspected</i>

00:26:15.733 --> 00:26:17.533
<i>that the kid might
have been abused.</i>

00:26:17.667 --> 00:26:18.767
<i> What's her full name?</i>

00:26:18.900 --> 00:26:20.000
<i> Anna Sarmiento.</i>

00:26:20.133 --> 00:26:21.767
<i>Why are so many people
looking for her?</i>

00:26:21.900 --> 00:26:23.700
<i> Did Anna do something wrong?</i>

00:26:23.833 --> 00:26:25.867
<i>Get ready, Grace.
I'm going to kidnap you.</i>

00:26:26.000 --> 00:26:28.267
<i> From now on,
</i>don't call me teacher, alright?

00:26:28.400 --> 00:26:29.267
<i> How are you related to her?</i>
